
1: You have sodo permission:

        sudo cp safe-rm /usr/local/bin/safe-rm
        sudo cp safe-rm /usr/local/bin/rm
        sudo cp dm /usr/local/bin/dm

        sudo touch /etc/safe-rm.conf

        touch ~/.config/safe-rm


2: You are a normal user, no root privileges

        cp safe-rm ~/local/bin/
        cp dm ~/local/bin/

        touch ~/.config/safe-rm

